Around the sky: Gemini meteor shower on the 14th will be a big one - Xinhua News Agency
As the last large-scale meteor shower of the year, the Gemini meteor shower, one of the three major meteor showers in the northern hemisphere, will hit the ground running on December 14, and friends who like it will be able to observe it in the middle of the night, Xinhua news agency said on December 12.
A meteor shower in the constellation Gemini was filmed in Qinghai on December 13, 2018 by Beijing astronomer An Jiu.
Most of the meteor shower's parent bodies are periodic comets, but the parent body of the Gemini meteor shower is the Apollo-type asteroid 3200 Phaeton.
The Gemini meteor shower is also the second meteor shower known not to have been "congenital" to a comet.
Shu Lipeng, a director of the Tianjin Astronomical Society and an expert on astronomy, said the meteor showers in Gemini usually occur at the end of the year, just like in the Happy New Year movie.
This meteor shower is known for its high flow rate and stability, and together with the quadrant meteor shower and the Perseus meteor shower, it is known as one of the three major meteor showers in the Northern Hemisphere.
A remarkable feature of the Gemini meteor showers is the slow velocity, rich color, and abundance of Martian meteors, suitable for both visual and astronomical photography beginners to shoot.
Tianjin astronomer Yang Jing captured a meteor shower in the constellation Gemini on December 13, 2020 in Tianjin.
Astronomers predict that this year's Gemini meteor shower will reach its peak at around 15:00 on December 14, with a maximum ZHR of 150 (the number of meteors seen per hour when the radiation point is just above the top of the head under ideal observation conditions).
Recommendation Index Chart for Meteor Rain in Gemini.
"Last year, people were impressed by the brilliant Gemini meteor showers, but this year's Gemini meteor showers will be disturbed by the moonlight and their brilliance will be slightly reduced.
The 14th day of the lunar calendar is November 11, and the moon is a full moon, bright moonlight can interfere with the observation, so that the moon will fall late in the night, at which time the radiation point of the meteor shower in Gemini will also rise relatively high.
Friends who like meteor showers can observe them in the hours after midnight, but watch out for cold and warmth.”
How can we observe as many meteors as possible?
"It is not advisable to observe in the city, but you can choose a high altitude, low lighting, open view to the northeast, in the suburbs or in the countryside, and then wait patiently for the moon to set for visual observation.
It should be noted that the Gemini meteor shower flows in all directions very large, do not always stare at the radiation point of the Gemini meteor shower when observing.
If you want to shoot a spectacular'meteor shower ', it is best to choose a wide angle, large aperture lens, using high ISO and maximum aperture when shooting.
Tripods, spare batteries, and shutters are also essential, based on stability and sustainability considerations.”
Shu Lipeng reminded.
3,200 newborn babies in Sabah with no life-saving paper
(API 11) The Sabah National Registry said it had been unable to issue birth certificates to newborn babies since the beginning of October because of the uselessness of specially-made forged paper stockpiles. The number of affected people has thus far reached 3,200.
However, the agency's director, Keru Aminus, has assured that all babies who have applied for birth certificates will be recorded in the system and will be re-issued when the forgery paper arrives next week.
At a news conference, he explained a ten-month-long story by a web-based media outlet about the printing problem in Sabah.
He said the problem arose two months ago and that Sarawak faced the same problem.
“One of the reasons is that Chinese manufacturers of specialty anti-counterfeiting paper have been affected by the epidemic, causing delays in arriving in China.”
He explained that the tamper-resistant paper used in Sabah was different from that used in other areas and could not be lent to stocks held in other states.
The latest batch of anti-counterfeiting paper arrived in Kuala Lumpur on June 6, and was handed over to the printing company for partial printing on August 8, Mr. Keru said.
“The bureau will send people to Kuala Lumpur next Thursday to pick up the goods and return to Sabah immediately for final printing, which is estimated to take two more working days (December 20) to get to the applicants.”
“We will notify applicants to go to the local branch offices to collect the report.”
He added that Sabah had issued 24,81 pieces of paper so far this year.
The amount of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake increased by 0.71 million tons this year.
Xinhua News Agency, Xining, Dec. 11 (reporters Lock Xiaofei and Zhang Hongxiang) reported from the Agriculture and Rural Department of Qinghai Province that the latest monitoring results showed that the amount of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake increased by 0.71 million tons this year compared to the previous year, reaching 10.85 million tons, more than 40 times the cumulative increase compared to the initial protection in 2002.
The naked carp of Qinghai Lake, popularly known as Huangyu, is a rare species of fish unique to the lake, and plays an important role in maintaining the ecological chain of water-fish-birds and biodiversity in the Qinghai Lake basin.
In the 1960s and 1970s, the number of naked carp in Qinghai Lake was drastically reduced due to the effects of large-scale human hunting and the declining environment in the naked carp breeding waters.
In 2004, the lake carp was listed as an endangered species in the Chinese Red List of Species.
Since 2003, Qinghai Province has implemented sealed lake fishing, prohibiting any units, collectives and individuals to fish for carp in the main rivers and tributaries of the Qinghai Lake and Lake District, and prohibiting the sale of carp and its products.
At the same time, the amount of naked carp resources in Qinghai Lake has been increasing year by year, through artificial propagation and discharge, as well as by cleaning up the channels through which the lake mainly flows into the lake, designing scientifically reasonable "fish passages," and other measures.
Yang Lin, deputy director of the Agriculture and Rural Department of Qinghai Province, said that so far, the Qinghai Lake carp has been artificially propagated and released nearly 180 million tail, contributing more than 23% to the recovery of the Qinghai Lake carp resources.
Qinghai-Sanjiang source area is an important ecological barrier and water reservoir area in China and even in Asia, while Qinghai-Lake is a natural barrier and ecological function area that controls the spread of western desertification to the east.
In order to protect the ecological environment in the source area of the Three Rivers and the waters of Qinghai Lake, protect aquatic wildlife and preserve the biological diversity of the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau, Qinghai has issued notices on the prohibition of fishing in the key waters of the Yangtze River, the Yellow River and the Qinghai Lake since this year, and has established a comprehensive system of "one river, one river, one lake" for the prohibition of fishing.
Students of the University of Zhejiang are the main participants in the academic year.
Wash hands with air, smell diseases, and search for haze sources with accuracy Yesterday evening, at the opening ceremony of the 2016 academic year of Zhejiang University, a series of brain-opening academic achievements were awarded.
The main researchers of these achievements are students.Their research covers various fields such as environment, machinery, energy, medical science, life science, humanities education, etc.The students have created many high-end inventions with application value from a curious point of view, some of which have won national and international awards.
Biosensors: Your Family Physician
Zhang Di-ming, a Ph.D. student at the School of Biomedical Engineering, demonstrated a biological sensor at the end of a smartphone that is only half the size of a smartphone.
“All you have to do is take a small breath, and the device will begin to detect your health from the gaseous components that you are exhaling.”
The sensor is connected to a smartphone, and the health report is displayed on the phone when the gas is exhaled, Zhang said.
Smart wristbands that can detect health status are commonly used to detect physical parameters such as temperature, pulse, etc.
The biosensors are made of a new material called graphene, which targets chemical elements and has a keen sense of smell that allows it to reflect health conditions more deeply and accurately.
Smart Surgery Lamp: Doctors' High-Powered Eyes
In addition to smartphones, the operating room also uses smart operating lights.
The invention won a silver medal at the 44th Geneva International Invention Fair this year.
The team of Zhu Linjing and Shen Junfei, M.Sc. in Optical and Electrical Sciences and Engineering, has opened a new way of thinking in the flaws of traditional surgical lamps, and invented an intelligent LED surgical shadowless lamp.
“Many diseases are detected early and can’t be removed, and they are related to the lights used in doctors’ operating rooms.”
If doctors don't see all the tumor tissue in time for early cancer screening, for example, then the cancer cells will spread,' Shen said.
The smart surgical lamp has four light panels that enhance the differentiation of different tissues under light by adjusting the spectrum.
During surgery, doctors can adjust the size, brightness, spectra, color uniformity, and shadowlessness of spots at any time, depending on the operation needs and personal habits.
The smart surgical light has been tested in Shao Yifu Hospital and Children's Hospital of Zhejiang University Medical School, and received good feedback.
Last October, the invention won first prize in the National Challenge Cup.
Wash your hands with air: water-saving and cool
Ordinary people wash their hands with water, rubbing soap on top, and squeezing hand-washing liquid, while classmates such as Li Kaizhang invented an “air hand-washing device.”
As long as we stand on the device's washstand, our weight can compress the air out.
"It's like an air cylinder.
The compressed air forms a fluid at the tap and combines with the water.
So we can wash our hands!'
Chromatography and bacterial residue experiments have shown that this method has the same effect as conventional hand washing.
This device only needs to rely on our own gravity as the driver, can guarantee the level of cleaning, but also save 90% water, the whole process is completely energy-efficient and environmentally friendly.
Last year, at the Second Global Summit on Major Challenges, the invention stood out from many of the world's top universities and won the only gold prize.
"China-Vietnam Joint Defense Exercise "Peace Relief - 2021" Completes" (PDF).
Chinese troops participating in the joint military exercise "Peace Relief - 2021" returned safely to Guangxi on the morning of December 12, Xinhua news agency said, marking the successful completion of the seven-day exercise.
In this joint exercise, the Chinese and Vietnamese armed forces focused on the humanitarian medical rescue as a major issue, tightened the mission of the guards to save the lives and help the wounded, and completed the joint guards command, joint field rescue, batch casualty disposal and other contents in accordance with the standards of actual warfare, and effectively enhanced the security capabilities of the two armies guards.
The results of the exercise were confirmed by the two armies.
"Through the exercise, Vietnamese military doctors have learned from Chinese military doctors about the organization and professional activities of the exercise, as well as about Chinese medical and security equipment," Director of the Vietnamese Exercise Steering Committee, Deputy Director of the General Administration of Logistics and Chief of Staff Nguyen Yuen-sheng said at the closing ceremony.
The results of the exercises proved the professional capabilities of the military and medical forces of the two countries in medical assistance and epidemic prevention and control.
Chen Chunming, the head of China's steering coordination group and deputy director of the Health Bureau of the Ministry of Logistics and Security of the Central Military Commission, said the exercise is another pioneering practice based on the successful joint outpatient clinic activities in 2018 and has a very important milestone significance.
During the exercise, the People's Liberation Army of China donated medical protective masks, medical protective clothing, rapid nucleic acid detection equipment and other health and epidemic prevention supplies to the Vietnamese People's Army.
Education time comment: save abducted children to rely on what?
If we compare the well-known public-interest slogan, "There is no killing without buying and selling," then, in a good environment without the need for "abduction," group-prevention and nationwide counter-abduction would make the act of abduction and selling unprofitable, risky, and costly, and such crimes would not happen again and again.
Recently, the Criminal Investigation Bureau of the Ministry of Public Security kidnapped and developed the missing children information urgently release platform online.
It is an Internet information platform created to establish an authoritative channel for publishing missing children's information and to find abducted children in a timely manner.
Listening to the app’s name, “Unity,” I felt warm.
New technology means not only the name “art and literature,” full of emotions, but also the application of information technology appropriately, practically, and effectively.
Kidnapping law enforcement, the primary goal is to find the kidnapped children, protect their personal safety and freedom.
The second is the trial and punishment of suspects.
The meaning of criminal punishment, from individual punishment, to social prevention, to legal education, can be summed up in many “big words.”
However, the victim's personal safety should be a priority before a kidnapping case is solved.
It is important to note, however, that in the case of a child who has been abducted and sold for the purpose of rescuing the child, the question of whether or not the child should be executed is a matter of great controversy and can be discussed with caution.
Based on the detection experience of such cases, traffickers are accustomed to moving away from the scene of the crime as soon as possible after the acquisition.
If the kidnapping operation is delayed by more than a minute, the child may be one step further away from the parent, and the difficulty of the case detection will increase by one point.
In this case, it is indeed a pragmatic action to come up with an effective way to help solve the case and find the child directly, such as a platform for “reunification.”
After all, “kidnapping” is a big task that requires the operation of an entire legal system.
The fight against crime, the protection of children's and parents' rights and interests, from the improvement of legislation to the protection of the judiciary, and the rigorous enforcement of laws, do not need to carry out the care of "protecting and supporting the weak".
Moreover, the prevention of child abduction, from the family to society, could be done better.
For example, in a common case, a family of three rests at the railway station, the parents fall asleep and wake up to find the child missing.
One cannot expect a two-year-old child to have sufficient self-protection skills, but as a parent of a young child, one should at least have a reasonable sense of protection.
Parents taking turns resting or placing their children under proper protection are the least that can be done to prevent their children from being abducted.
From the other side of the police's fight against the crime of kidnapping and selling, the purchase of kidnapped children should also be paid attention to and punished.
A single illegal act is often just a ring in a long chain.
According to the Criminal Law of our country, the statutory penalty for the crime of child abduction and trafficking is five years' imprisonment; the circumstances are particularly serious and can lead to the death penalty and confiscation of property.
The crime of child abduction and trafficking is clearly a more serious crime under the trend of "minimizing the punishment" with a high penalty point and the highest penalty.
However, there are still many cases of trafficking every year.
It can be seen that some people are lagging behind in the concept of child-rearing and legal awareness is weak.
Legal education for this section of the population should be pursued simultaneously.
To effectively control the crime of trafficking, we cannot rely solely on strict official law enforcement.
If the abduction "market" exists widely, the abductors are motivated to innovate the means of abduction, forming a "fighting" situation with law enforcement officials, the abduction action will be ineffective.
Thus, removing backward notions and disseminating common sense of law will also help to eradicate the crime of child abduction and child bribery.
At the end of the democratic summit, Biden says the fire of freedom will never be extinguished
The online Summit for Democracy, convened by US President Barack Obama and attended by governments and civil-society and private-sector leaders from 110 countries around the world, wrapped up on Friday (December 10).
In his closing remarks, Biden said that the fire of freedom burns in the hearts of everyone in the world and that authoritarian regimes can never extinguish it.
He also says he plans to hold the second global “democracy summit” next year.
Taiwanese government representative and councillor Tang Feng and Hong Kong democratic human rights activist Luo Guanzhong, who is currently in exile in the UK, also spoke at the summit the following day.
"We know how difficult the work is before us," Biden said.
But we also know that we can meet the challenge, because as I said before, as this summit has shown, the democratic world is everywhere.
Autocratic regimes can never extinguish the flame of freedom, which burns in the hearts of people all over the world, and around the world.”
He added that defending democracy requires a concerted effort on the part of society as a whole.
“As leaders of governments, we have a responsibility to listen to our citizens, to strengthen the shield of democracy, to push for reform, to achieve transparent and accountable governance, to better withstand the forces of despotism’s buffers and shocks, and to those who want to pursue power nakedly before the public interest,” he said.
The second day of the “democracy summit” focused on defending human rights, consolidating democracy and countering authoritarianism, and countering digital authoritarianism and affirming democratic values.
The day falls on International Human Rights Day.
In his opening remarks, UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan said the cause of democracy faces global challenges, particularly those posed by emerging digital technologies.
“The time has come to reaffirm our common values and positions and the resilience of democracy,” he said.
This requires deepening social dialogue, addressing inequalities, fighting corruption, renewing social contracts, investing in quality education, and expanding opportunities for women and girls.
It also requires a firm condemnation of all forms of populism, nationalism, and extremism, including the use of all the tools provided by the technological revolution.”
Hong Kong's democratic human rights activist, Mr Lau, addressed the summit in a pre-recorded video, reminding participants of the continuing concerns about the human rights situation in Hong Kong and among minorities such as the Uighurs and Tibetans.
“The world has long accepted China’s rise without a mechanism to hold it accountable,” he said.
That is why politicians and civil-society leaders must work together.
We must use all the resources at our disposal to ensure that the revival of democracy is our first priority.”
He also called on the free world to unite against the threat of the Communist Party of China.
“Perhaps some of you are afraid to annoy the President, perhaps some of you don’t want to lose the Chinese market, perhaps some of you don’t recognize the threat to our democratic values,” he said.
And that's why we failed.
That is why we must change.”
In a roundtable discussion on “Combating Digital Dictatorship and Affirming Democratic Values,” Tang Feng, a member of the Taiwan Executive Yuan, released a video statement emphasizing that Taiwan stands at the forefront of the struggle against authoritarianism and authoritarianism.
He also shared his experience of how to combat the new crop epidemic through information transparency and building mutual trust.
"At a time when Taiwan's democracy is on the rise, we have always stood firmly at the forefront of the global fight against authoritarianism and have played a leading role in promoting global freedom, democracy and human rights," he said.
During the epidemic, authoritarian governments everywhere justified human rights violations in the name of public health and collective interests, and global democracy showed signs of retreat.
In Taiwan, however, we don’t have to seal the city to control the epidemic, and we don’t have to go underground to defeat false information.”
On the second day of the summit, the US Treasury announced legal sanctions against 15 individuals and 10 entities in China, North Korea, and several other countries that have been found to be committing serious human rights violations, as well as investment restrictions on a Chinese company that has been found to be using surveillance technology to assist in human rights violations.
