Professor Lau Jun-yi was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Education, Professor Chen Kai-shin was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science, Professor Shui II Nakamura was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science, Professor Li Lan-chuan was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science, Professor Li Yu-liang was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Business Administration, Professor Chu Li-lan was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science, and Ms Jiang Chaohui was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Science.
In her speech, Ms. Ou firstly extended warm congratulations and high regards to the seven distinguished persons who have been awarded honorary doctorates. They have achieved remarkable achievements in different fields, respectively, and made outstanding contributions to the development of the country and the progress of the world. At the same time, Ms. Ou extended her most sincere congratulations to the graduates and their parents, as well as sincere respects to the dedicated and academically excellent faculty and staff of the University.
Speaking at the ceremony, Professor Sun Yi-feng, Chairman of the Faculty of Humanities, said that Professor Zunyi is a world-renowned economist renowned for his outstanding academic achievements and forward-looking educational ideas.
In addition to his achievements in economic development, economic growth and the East Asian economy, he is a visionary educational leader.
In short, he has excelled in many fields.
Sun Yifeng, who read Shuji Nakamura's eulogy, said Professor Nakamura is a pioneer in sustainable energy technology.
He was one of three winners of the 2014 Nobel Prize in Physics for his invention of the blue light emitting diode (LED).
Professor Nakamura's invention has not only revolutionized the lighting industry, but has also contributed greatly to the well-being of humanity by producing white luminous diodes that are now widely used in everyday life and industrial production.
As a pioneer in China's artificial liver industry, Professor Li has created a unique and effective Li's artificial liver system, which has made a major breakthrough in the treatment of severe hepatitis liver failure and significantly reduced the mortality rate of liver failure, Sun said.
In the battle against new coronary pneumonia, she and her team proposed a "four-anti-two balance" program and brought three technologies: artificial liver, micro-ecology, and stem cells, which significantly improved the rate of serious rescue.
When Sun Yifeng reads Li's words, he says he has laid the foundation for innovative research in operations management, shaped the thinking of supply chain theory and practice, and radically changed business patterns around the world.
Li Yuliang is famous for the concept of long whip effect in popular operational management and explores the measures to deal with this phenomenon.
Today, in countries with epidemics and strained economies, the whip effect is becoming more pronounced, causing severe disruption to supply chains.
Li Yuliang's far-sighted research, such as the transportation of coal in the snow, helps the industry to cope with the difficulties, and thus brings great social value.
In her scientific research, she has discovered a breakthrough and innovative dyeing technique for preparing samples, and enjoys a high reputation among her domestic and international scientific peers, Sun said as she read out her words of appreciation.
She has earned important honorary titles such as Fellow of the International Eurasian Academy of Sciences for her remarkable scientific achievements, and has earned the high status she deserves in the Temple of Science and Technology of the world for her brilliant achievements.
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Vice-President of the Chinese Medicine Research Institute of the University of Australia, Dr Chan Xin Xuan, said that Professor Chen has been engaged in drug research and development for more than 40 years, and his outstanding scientific achievements and important contributions to the country, Macao, Macao University and key national laboratories have given him a high international status and prestige.
His active role in promoting the development of Chinese medicine in Macao and the Gulf Region fully reflects his commitment to the development of Chinese medicine in the country.
The President of the Australian University of Science and Technology (AUST), Mr Su Cheng Chung, said in his remarks that Ms Jiang had participated in the development of major inventions and patents.To date, more than 15 inventions and patents have been accumulated relating to storage virtualization, navigation, file systems and power management.These inventions and patents are highly usable and widely used to enhance the convenience of human life.
As an accomplished inventor, Ms. Jiang is often able to simplify and popularize advanced technology and theory.
At the end of the ceremony, Chen Kai-shek read a thank you speech on behalf of the honorary doctor.
He was pleased to see that Macau and the Bay Area had set a good example in the pharmaceutical industry: from the establishment of the first National Key Laboratory for Quality Research in Chinese Medicine to the thriving development of the Bay Area's Chinese medicine, the University had contributed greatly to the integration of outstanding talents in the field of Chinese medicine in the Bay Area.
Furthermore, he believes that the management team at the University of Australia is far-sighted, not only providing academically sound research ground for students, but also bringing a lot of responsible people to society.
He is honoured to be able to engage in exchanges and cooperation with the University and sincerely congratulates the University on its achievements in recent years.
Yunnan: Coordination and Standardization of Rural Public Welfare Position Management - Xinhua News Agency
Xinhua news agency, Kunming, Dec. 12, by wire (journalist Lin Beifeng) In order to continuously improve employment assistance for people who have escaped poverty and consolidate the achievements of expanding the fight against poverty, Yunnan province has issued policies to promote rural revitalization and the management of rural public welfare jobs, helping to promote rural revitalization in a comprehensive manner.
At present, Yunnan province has developed 44,830,000 rural public welfare posts for the employment of rural hard-pressed groups such as the labor force that has been lifted out of poverty, and plays an important role in helping the people who have been lifted out of poverty to achieve higher employment and income, consolidate the achievements of fighting poverty and effectively enhance the capacity of various public services in the countryside, the relevant head of the Yunnan Provincial Office of Human Rights and Social Affairs said.
The new regulations are jointly issued by the seven departments of Yunnan People's Association, Village Revitalization, and Finance.They are mainly unified standards for the scope of recruitment of rural public welfare posts at the grassroots level, the management of funds, the development of posts, and the management of posts.
In terms of job development and establishment, the new rules are clear and are based on the principles of "posting according to need, assigning people to posts, dynamic management, total control", "who develops, who uses, who is responsible" and "one person per post, voluntary openness and unified management".
The recruitment procedure must follow the steps of announcement, declaration, examination, public announcement, hiring, pre-employment training and arranging for promotion.
In addition, the new regulations also clarify the specific responsibilities of the main development departments of rural public welfare posts, the subsidy standards for rural public welfare posts and the subsidy methods, stipulate that each rural public welfare post development department should purchase accident and injury business insurance for the settlers of rural public welfare posts, and require the relevant departments to monitor the distribution of subsidies for rural public welfare posts on a regular basis.
