48 hours of nucleic acid negative, establish " buffer zone " State Council Joint Defense Joint Control Mechanism requests to strengthen port city epidemic prevention and control - Zhejiang website
The State Council's Joint Defense and Control Mechanism issued a notice on strengthening the control and prevention of pneumonia outbreaks in port cities on December 11, Xinhua news agency reported.It requires persons who recently leave land border port cities (except those connected with ports in Hong Kong and Macao) to have negative certificates for testing nucleic acid within 48 hours, and carry out at least one test of nucleic acid after arriving at the land border port city.
According to the notice, the above-mentioned requirement is for a period of time from the date when the port city scope is determined and announced by the provinces and municipalities to March 15, 2022.
In addition, the Notice also proposes that a port city subject to conditions may study the establishment of epidemic prevention and control buffer zones within its jurisdiction.
For some port cities, cross-border border trade is the main economic pillar of the local economy, and people from both sides travel frequently, the head of the Bureau of Disease Prevention and Control of the State Health Commission said.
By implementing a differentiated management policy for the sub-divisions, from one outbreak prevention and control line to two outbreak prevention and control lines, it is hoped that the frontier will be moved forward, the outbreak prevention and control risks will be reduced, and the greatest effect will be achieved with the least social impact and the lowest social cost.
Recently, there have been many cases of indigenous aggregation epidemics in China, all of which are imported from overseas through port cities.
The above-mentioned notice points out that this exposes some local epidemic surveillance early warning in a timely manner, closed-circuit management of high-risk position personnel is not implemented, regular flow of nucleic acid testing in the form, cold chain items in various links can not be eliminated, centralized isolation site management is not standardized, epidemic emergency management is not scientifically accurate, and so on.
In response to the notification request, nine aspects such as improving the mechanism for the prevention and control of epidemics in port cities, improving the early warning system for the monitoring of epidemics, and implementing border control measures have been put into practice.
The notification stressed that port cities should conduct simultaneous research and deployment of epidemic prevention and control and the protection of people's livelihoods, announce and open the hotline for people's livelihoods protection, regularly identify hidden problems in the supply and price of basic necessities of life, and promptly solve and actively respond to the outstanding problems reported by the public.
According to the notification, the port cities referred to therein include the counties (cities, districts, flags) where the open land, water and air ports are located, the cities (territories, states, unions) where the ports are located and the cities directly under the Central Government.
South African Doctor: Omicron is contagious, but mostly mild
Many South African doctors and medical experts believe that the new crown virus Omicron strain causes less disease than the Delta strain, although it spreads at a faster rate.
A group of more than 5,000 doctors in South Africa's Haute-Garonne province reported that they are treating new crown patients with mild symptoms such as body pain and coughing that resemble influenza, the Associated Press reported.
Dr. Unben Pillay, the organization's director, says he sees dozens of patients every day, but no patients need to be hospitalized.
“They were able to control the disease at home,” Pillay said, “and most recovered within 10 to 14 days of isolation.”
He says this includes the elderly and those with health problems who are more likely to become seriously ill from coronary virus infections.
In contrast, he said, in the last wave of the Delta outbreak, he treated patients with new crowns who had "difficulty breathing and low blood oxygen levels.
Many will be hospitalized in a few days.”
Other doctors shared similar experiences two weeks after the first report of Omicron mutant strains in southern Africa.
Although it will take several weeks to collect enough data, doctors' observations and early evidence provide some clues.
According to the South African National Institute of Infectious Diseases, only 30% of new coronary heart disease patients hospitalized in recent weeks were severe, half the rate of the previous wave; the average length of hospitalization was reduced from 8 to 2.8 days; and only 3% of new coronary heart disease patients died recently, compared to 20% in early-onset outbreaks in South Africa.
“At present, there are almost all indications that it is a mild disease,” said Willem Hanekom, director of the African Health Institute, citing data from the National Institutes of Infectious Diseases and other reports.
"It's still early days and we need to get the later data," he added.
Normally, hospitalizations and deaths occur later, and we only enter this epidemic in two weeks.”
Meanwhile, scientists around the world are observing the number of cases and hospitalization rates while testing the effectiveness of current vaccines and treatments.
Although Delta is still the world's leading new crown virus strain, Omicron cases are occurring in dozens of countries, with South Africa as the centre of the epidemic.
According to health officials, the number of new cases detected in the first week of December in the province of Hohenzollern increased by 400%, with tests showing more than 90% of cases of Omikyong variants.
Educational Thinking: How the University Examination Makes the " Hegemon " and the " Leftovers " Each Get Its Own - Official Website
Three students from Lanzhou Jiaotong University wrote a letter to the head of the university, reflecting the confusion about the university examination, and proposed to improve the difficulty of the examination, changing the examination questions, so that the examination really reflects the students' actual level of aspiration.
Indeed, university exams have long been a “hot topic.”
On the university campus, students come from all over the world, with varying levels of ability, plus varying degrees of learning and studying conditions.
It is inevitable that there will be different feelings when evaluating groups with such diverse characteristics.
Of course, if the test questions are of a single type, repetition rates are high, the subject is too simple, it will inevitably cause a completely different feeling.
Students who do not study hard may be able to pass the exam by concentrating on assault. If you think of other ways, it is possible to achieve half the effect.
In this way, “study residue” can pass and even score high if it is not invested in; “study bully” never drops out of class, has good homework and notes, and does not score high on exams.
In this way, the students of Lanzhou University reflect the problems that exist in the university examination is not without reason, believe that the situation does not exist only Lanzhou University.
In this sense, praise the three students who wrote the letter.
In fact, everyone who has attended university knows that it is not uncommon for students to rush to prepare for exams, think of various ways to "take up" exam questions from their teachers, try to delineate the scope of the examination, and seek "focused guidance" before the examination. It is also not uncommon for students to take notes in the examination and ask their teachers to raise their hand after the examination.
In the author's view, as a kind of teaching quality assessment guideline, the measurement of a university examination's qualification or not lies more in the teacher's comprehensive grasp of teaching and learning, and the scientific proposition on this basis.
In the undergraduate stage of university, the majors begin to be subdivided, and many of the major courses are based on basic knowledge.
There is no doubt that mastering the basic knowledge of a subject is the content of the university examination.
The undergraduate knowledge is basically the basic theory and common sense of the subject, the space of change from the point of knowledge is not large, it is basically fixed.
As one teacher put it, “The basics of university mathematics, 20 years ago, are still being studied, or the focus.”
However, the knowledge point is basically unchanged, does not mean that the test question type is single, the test question repeated.
In many universities, examinations are usually composed of a group of questions, then by senior subject teachers to co-ordinate the examination papers, examination papers also by all teachers of the subject participate, so as to overcome to some extent the repetition of the examination questions.
However, to prepare a set of test questions in accordance with teaching and learning practice, the subjects are difficult to present a normal distribution according to the student's overall learning situation, it is also necessary to master the teaching situation comprehensively, comprehensively analyze the degree of student's learning, so as to make the test proposition to the difficulty and the type of the dynamic grasp, can highlight the basic knowledge examination, but also take into account the ability examination, and at the same time carry out the innovative design of the type of the question.
The examination is the commanding rod of university education, what kind of examination, students will have the corresponding preparation program, will affect the university education's effectiveness in the long run.
To the students' letter of recommendation, Lanzhou Jiao University attaches great importance, has deployed the correction program in the whole school.
Teaching units shall be required to organize teachers to carry out research and self-examination of course-ending examinations against each other, to formulate examination questionnaire propositions and related systems, and at the same time to strengthen the supervision and examination of examination questionnaire propositions and examination links, to fine-tune the assessment of achievements, and to strengthen the comprehensive examination of all links of course teaching.
It is important to note that in order for a teacher to have a complete grasp of the teaching situation, he must not only digest the teaching content, but also digest the student's learning situation, and digest both the teaching and learning situation, so that the teaching and learning will interact better and form a positive interaction, and the examination will be more in line with the actual situation, so that the hegemon and the scum will get their way.
