The government encourages universities to set up innovation and entrepreneurship credits, and gives priority to supporting students who excel in innovation and entrepreneurship practices to transfer to professional fields.
In order to improve the consciousness and ability of teachers to innovate and start-up education, teachers in universities and colleges should take at least two months every two years to engage in vocational training in industry enterprises.
The Office of Education of the Autonomous Region demands Guangxi universities to implement the university students' innovation and entrepreneurship training program in depth, striving to make every university student participate in an innovation and entrepreneurship training program while in school.
